WEBVTT

00:03.742 --> 00:04.091
.

00:04.134 --> 00:05.570
[dramatic music]

00:05.614 --> 00:07.007
- Drop his weapon!

00:07.050 --> 00:10.662
- Roy is gone, and you
gotta accept what happened.

00:10.706 --> 00:13.230
The feds will put
his face on the wall,

00:13.274 --> 00:15.058
but they will never
see or hear a thing.

00:15.102 --> 00:16.799
- Like it never happened.

00:16.842 --> 00:18.496
- But it did happen.

00:18.540 --> 00:21.586
Now you got to make peace,
live your life.

00:23.066 --> 00:25.112
- Hailey, will you marry me?

00:25.155 --> 00:27.201
- Yes.

00:34.121 --> 00:36.558
- Detective.
- Detective.

00:38.081 --> 00:40.388
- I got you something.

00:40.431 --> 00:42.303
- Hm.

00:42.346 --> 00:43.739
- So I guess I'll see you
at home.

00:43.782 --> 00:45.132
- Mm-hmm.

00:52.661 --> 00:53.749
- Yo, you guys know

00:53.792 --> 00:55.925
we all know
you're doing it, right?

00:55.968 --> 00:57.535
- Doing it?
- Doing it.

00:57.579 --> 00:58.710
What's up?

00:58.754 --> 01:00.103
- Jay and Hailey
are moving in together.

01:00.147 --> 01:01.887
Tonight, I think, yeah?

01:01.931 --> 01:03.541
I'm a trained observer.

01:03.585 --> 01:05.456
- You do know we all know
you're together, right?

01:05.500 --> 01:06.762
- Yeah, I'm aware of that.

01:06.805 --> 01:08.155
What I don't get is
why that's a non-event,

01:08.198 --> 01:09.721
but this is a thing.

01:09.765 --> 01:11.245
We've been staying at each
other's apartments for months.

01:11.288 --> 01:13.464
- Well, 'cause then
you were just, like, doing it.

01:13.508 --> 01:15.336
Now you're doing it.
- It's the same thing.

01:15.379 --> 01:16.728
Well, it's definitely
not the same thing.

01:16.772 --> 01:18.382
- For instance, did you know
that sometimes women

01:18.426 --> 01:20.384
use the medicine cabinet
to store medicine?

01:21.951 --> 01:24.040
- Hailey, got a sec?

01:24.084 --> 01:25.302
- Let me tell
you something right now.

01:25.346 --> 01:26.869
I look around this room,
you know what

01:26.912 --> 01:27.870
the first thing I think is?

01:29.828 --> 01:32.179
Here's a bunch
of relationship experts.

01:36.183 --> 01:38.968
- Making some
big changes in your life.

01:39.011 --> 01:41.101
- Yeah, I am.

01:41.144 --> 01:42.537
We are.

01:45.192 --> 01:48.151
- Okay, apparently,
the FBI got a tip.

01:48.195 --> 01:51.198
Passed it onto CPD.

01:51.241 --> 01:53.591
Seems a citizen
spotted Roy Walton

01:53.635 --> 01:56.420
at a hardware store in Dallas.

01:56.464 --> 01:58.596
- That seems unlikely.

01:58.640 --> 02:01.773
- Yeah, chances are,
the FBI knows it's not true.

02:01.817 --> 02:04.428
They're just dropping it
in our laps

02:04.472 --> 02:07.127
to see who flinches.

02:07.170 --> 02:12.958
Look, whatever it is,
I wanted you to know because...

02:13.002 --> 02:15.483
[apprehensive music]

02:15.526 --> 02:17.137
Now, more than ever,
it's important

02:17.180 --> 02:18.442
that we stay the course.

02:18.486 --> 02:20.357
Do nothing unusual.

02:20.401 --> 02:23.578
Say nothing to anyone.

02:27.190 --> 02:28.713
- Yep.

02:34.458 --> 02:35.938
- All units in the citywide,

02:35.981 --> 02:38.636
bottle gang going at it,
77th and Berkeley.

02:38.680 --> 02:40.856
Armed robbery in progress,
4800 South Drake.

02:40.899 --> 02:41.987
- Another one?

02:42.031 --> 02:43.641
- More calls coming in
on Drake.

02:43.685 --> 02:45.643
Reports of an explosion,
CFD responding.

02:45.687 --> 02:47.036
- Another one.

02:47.079 --> 02:49.473
- 50-21 Henry, plainclothes
officers responding.

02:49.517 --> 02:52.259
Advise units to proceed
with extreme caution.

02:52.302 --> 02:55.218
[intense music]

02:55.262 --> 02:59.831
♪

02:59.875 --> 03:02.225
50-21 Henry and George
on the scene.

03:02.269 --> 03:03.879
Call's bona fide,
keep the cars rolling.

03:06.882 --> 03:08.100
- Police, where are they?

03:08.144 --> 03:09.493
- Took off towards Pulaski.
- Three of them?

03:09.537 --> 03:11.060
- Yeah, they're gone,
they blasted the doors,

03:11.103 --> 03:12.148
took the cash, took off.

03:12.192 --> 03:13.367
- Getaway car?

03:13.410 --> 03:14.759
- Uh, four door dark,
that's all I got.

03:14.803 --> 03:16.196
They're over here.

03:16.239 --> 03:17.501
- Oh my God, help her!
Please help her!

03:17.545 --> 03:19.808
- Okay, okay, okay! Okay.

03:19.851 --> 03:22.289
- Oh, God! Get it out!
- No, no, no!

03:22.332 --> 03:23.942
No, no, don't touch it,
don't touch it!

03:23.986 --> 03:25.335
If you pull it out,
it could kill her.

03:25.379 --> 03:26.554
What's your daughter's name?

03:26.597 --> 03:28.904
- Sydney. Sydney Rose.

03:28.947 --> 03:30.340
- Okay, Sydney Rose,
we got you, we got you.

03:30.384 --> 03:31.820
Do you hear me?
It's gonna be okay.

03:31.863 --> 03:33.778
50-21 George emergency,
roll an ambo to Drake.

03:33.822 --> 03:36.041
I got got a tender age female.
She's got a projectile wound.

03:36.085 --> 03:37.478
Advise Med, extremely critical.

03:37.521 --> 03:40.132
Hey, it's gonna be okay.
Stay with us, stay with us.

03:40.176 --> 03:41.308
- It's okay.

03:41.351 --> 03:44.267
[mother crying]

03:44.311 --> 03:49.272
♪

03:51.535 --> 03:52.754
- Same MO?
- Yeah.

03:52.797 --> 03:54.538
We're pulling video
to prove it,

03:54.582 --> 03:56.932
but it's our robbery crew,
definitely.

03:56.975 --> 03:58.281
Same as the last three.

03:58.325 --> 03:59.761
- The armored car pulls up
to service the bank.

03:59.804 --> 04:01.110
One of the offenders
pulls in front of them

04:01.153 --> 04:02.807
with a truck to block
them in and then boom.

04:02.851 --> 04:04.505
Two offenders pull up
behind him,

04:04.548 --> 04:06.158
blow the door before the guards
have time to engage.

04:06.202 --> 04:07.551
They reach inside,
it's grab and go.

04:07.595 --> 04:08.987
- Made out
with 800 grand, give or take.

04:09.031 --> 04:10.859
We got a flash out
on the getaway car.

04:10.902 --> 04:12.469
- Truck's hot?

04:12.513 --> 04:14.384
- Yeah, it's confirmed stolen
last night down in Chatham.

04:14.428 --> 04:15.777
We're working on surveillance.

04:15.820 --> 04:17.387
- We recovered a coffee cup
on the console,

04:17.431 --> 04:18.562
we'll see if anything pops.

04:18.606 --> 04:20.085
It's going through
DNA and prints now.

04:20.129 --> 04:21.739
- We'll find the route
that the armored vehicle

04:21.783 --> 04:23.524
took to get here,
we'll pull traffic cams.

04:23.567 --> 04:24.742
- All right,
do we know what kind

04:24.786 --> 04:26.222
of explosives these guys used?

04:26.266 --> 04:28.485
- Bomb and Arson, they're
sending scraps and remnants

04:28.529 --> 04:31.271
to Joliet, but it sounds like
they're pretty backed up.

04:31.314 --> 04:33.708
- Well, get up there in person,
light a fire under their ass.

04:33.751 --> 04:36.537
We got blood in the street now.
Let's get on top of this.

04:39.366 --> 04:42.282
[suspenseful music]

04:42.325 --> 04:49.463
♪

04:54.076 --> 04:55.338
- How's the little girl?

04:55.382 --> 04:57.297
- She's out of surgery in Med,
touch and go.

04:57.340 --> 04:58.602
- All right, three men.

04:58.646 --> 05:01.083
Body armor, big-ass weapons,
professional crew.

05:01.126 --> 05:02.476
Everything's a match.

05:02.519 --> 05:05.348
Body type, weaponry, MO.

05:05.392 --> 05:06.915
This is definitely our crew.

05:06.958 --> 05:09.483
- Yeah, they use stolen
vehicles, torch them.

05:09.526 --> 05:10.614
- We got no footage
of them stealing

05:10.658 --> 05:12.181
the truck that they used.

05:12.224 --> 05:13.965
- And the prints on the coffee
cup came back to the owner

05:14.009 --> 05:16.141
of the vehicle, he's happy
as hell to get his truck back.

05:16.185 --> 05:17.665
Sends his regards.

05:17.708 --> 05:18.927
- We eliminated the possibility

05:18.970 --> 05:20.450
of them having
a man on the inside.

05:20.494 --> 05:22.147
Every robbery
has been a different

05:22.191 --> 05:23.540
armored truck company.

05:23.584 --> 05:25.847
- Look, we got bombs going off
middle of the city,

05:25.890 --> 05:28.240
broad daylight, all on video
more clear than I get

05:28.284 --> 05:29.981
trying to watch the Sox.

05:30.025 --> 05:34.377
So please, please tell me we're
not circling the drain here.

05:34.421 --> 05:36.553
- Oh, I don't think we are.

05:36.597 --> 05:38.468
Joliet ID'd
the explosive material

05:38.512 --> 05:41.515
used in the robbery
as military grade C4.

05:41.558 --> 05:43.299
And the chemical footprint
matches a batch

05:43.343 --> 05:44.822
stolen from DF Tubbs.

05:44.866 --> 05:45.997
- The army base?

05:46.041 --> 05:47.695
- Army reserve.
It's out in the boonies.

05:47.738 --> 05:49.827
- Yeah, these devices are
military style sticky bombs.

05:49.871 --> 05:51.220
They go way back.

05:51.263 --> 05:53.353
We used them to bust
into tanks in World War II.

05:53.396 --> 05:54.919
Okay, so the robbers,

05:54.963 --> 05:56.617
they build the devices
a certain way.

05:56.660 --> 05:59.576
The lab reverse engineers them,
and this is their best guess.

05:59.620 --> 06:03.363
They take C4, and they
pack it into the light bulbs.

06:03.406 --> 06:06.017
Then they wrap the light bulbs
in these cotton socks,

06:06.061 --> 06:08.411
then they dip the cotton sock
into this gunk.

06:08.455 --> 06:10.631
It's--it's the sticky
stuff made from...

06:10.674 --> 06:13.285
- Boiled tree bark.

06:13.329 --> 06:14.722
- Yeah, that's right.

06:16.114 --> 06:18.290
- Juniper trees.

06:18.334 --> 06:20.075
- No, that's not right.

06:20.118 --> 06:23.383
It's made from, um, hold on.

06:23.426 --> 06:25.428
Eastern red cedar.

06:25.472 --> 06:27.430
Which is not actually a cedar.

06:27.474 --> 06:29.084
It's a juniper.

06:29.127 --> 06:30.738
It's the only
variation of juniper

06:30.781 --> 06:33.001
that grows in Illinois.

06:33.044 --> 06:38.702
♪

06:38.746 --> 06:40.530
- They should be down in a sec.

06:40.574 --> 06:42.706
And thanks a lot
for coming our way.

06:42.750 --> 06:44.447
- You guys are doing us
a solid.

06:44.491 --> 06:46.797
Wouldn't mind
some answers ourselves.

06:46.841 --> 06:51.062
Not every day 10 bricks of C4
walks out the door.

06:51.106 --> 06:54.065
- I really,
really hope that's true.

06:54.109 --> 06:55.240
There you go.

06:55.284 --> 06:56.546
- Staff Sergeant.

06:56.590 --> 06:58.026
- Detectives, here's the list
you asked for.

06:58.069 --> 07:00.028
The manifest of every
man and woman who was

07:00.071 --> 07:03.901
on base the weekend
the C4 was stolen.

07:03.945 --> 07:05.512
- Whoa.
- That's the problem.

07:05.555 --> 07:07.862
There were
4,000 airmen and personnel

07:07.905 --> 07:09.167
from other services
in and out of there.

07:09.211 --> 07:11.387
We were doing a huge
training exercise.

07:11.431 --> 07:12.997
- Probably not a coincidence.

07:13.041 --> 07:14.912
- That would have been the time
to do something like this.

07:14.956 --> 07:17.872
We gave up trying to figure
out who ran off with it.

07:17.915 --> 07:19.439
- Yeah, sure,
thanks for your time.

07:19.482 --> 07:20.744
- Happy hunting.

07:22.093 --> 07:23.138
- How are we gonna get
through this list?

07:23.181 --> 07:25.445
There's so many names.

07:25.488 --> 07:27.142
- I'm just looking for one.

07:27.185 --> 07:34.149
♪

07:38.240 --> 07:39.763
- Elliot Knox?

07:39.807 --> 07:41.548
What, you know him?

07:43.332 --> 07:44.725
- Warsaj Kalay.

07:46.291 --> 07:47.205
- What?

07:48.685 --> 07:50.078
- Afghanistan.

07:58.347 --> 07:58.478
.

07:58.521 --> 08:02.394
- Okay, so,
outside of the Taliban,

08:02.438 --> 08:04.222
there aren't many people
who would use this

08:04.266 --> 08:06.181
exact recipe
to make a sticky bomb.

08:06.224 --> 08:10.925
One of them is Elliot Knox.

08:10.968 --> 08:14.537
The other one is me.

08:14.581 --> 08:16.583
Knox and I did two tours
together in Afghanistan.

08:16.626 --> 08:17.888
He was EOD.

08:17.932 --> 08:20.804
His job was to disable
and defeat enemy IEDs.

08:20.848 --> 08:22.153
We hit it off at first.

08:22.197 --> 08:24.155
We're both from Chicago,
and I thought

08:24.199 --> 08:25.722
he was a good guy.

08:25.766 --> 08:28.159
- And then?

08:28.203 --> 08:31.423
- Turned out, not a good guy.

08:31.467 --> 08:33.164
- We scrubbed Knox.

08:33.208 --> 08:34.426
He's had a hard time of it.

08:34.470 --> 08:35.906
Divorce, bankruptcy,
bounced around a lot.

08:35.950 --> 08:37.212
It was hard to pin down an LKA

08:37.255 --> 08:38.692
'cause he's had trouble
paying rent.

08:38.735 --> 08:40.345
- Doesn't have much of a sheet.

08:40.389 --> 08:41.608
- Nah, he was rolled
up eight years ago

08:41.651 --> 08:42.913
for a five-finger discount.

08:42.957 --> 08:44.349
He walked out
of a QuickMart with a hoagie.

08:44.393 --> 08:45.829
That's it, clean ever since.

08:45.873 --> 08:47.657
- So I haven't seen this
guy in 12 or 13 years,

08:47.701 --> 08:50.225
but he's a pretty good match
for one of our offenders.

08:50.268 --> 08:51.966
This guy right here.

08:52.009 --> 08:54.316
I'd bet almost anything
Knox stole the C4.

08:54.359 --> 08:57.580
He's making the bombs, and he's
using them to rob the trucks.

08:57.624 --> 08:59.843
- He know you're a cop?

08:59.887 --> 09:01.453
- There's no reason
why he would.

09:01.497 --> 09:03.717
- All right, so let's track
him down, see if you're right.

09:10.941 --> 09:12.073
- Don't think we've met.

09:12.116 --> 09:13.857
- Halstead, 75th Rangers.

09:13.901 --> 09:17.034
- Alex Argrett, 5th Cav.

09:17.078 --> 09:18.906
- Hey, thank you.

09:18.949 --> 09:20.429
- Losing an arm?

09:20.472 --> 09:21.517
- No, man, for signing up
to go someplace

09:21.561 --> 09:23.388
where you could lose an arm.

09:23.432 --> 09:24.999
- Glad you found us.

09:25.042 --> 09:27.436
Yeah, actually, I've been
to this group a few times.

09:27.479 --> 09:28.785
When I first got home.

09:28.829 --> 09:30.395
I don't know why
I stopped coming.

09:30.439 --> 09:33.137
- Welcome back then.

09:33.181 --> 09:34.617
- That true?

09:34.661 --> 09:36.793
Jay really used to come here?

09:36.837 --> 09:39.579
- I don't know.

09:39.622 --> 09:41.581
There he is. There's Knox.

09:41.624 --> 09:45.019
- Heavenly father, bless
and protect these veterans.

09:45.062 --> 09:50.067
Gave so much for so many.

09:50.111 --> 09:52.113
All right, here we go.

09:52.156 --> 09:53.723
all:
Not for kings.

09:53.767 --> 09:55.638
Not for glory.

09:55.682 --> 09:57.901
For the one next to me.

09:57.945 --> 09:59.686
- All right, let's get
some chairs.

10:06.649 --> 10:09.086
- Halstead, it's Knox.

10:09.130 --> 10:10.261
- Knox?

10:10.305 --> 10:12.960
Dude, small world.

10:14.918 --> 10:16.703
- Hey, bro,
if you want me to split,

10:16.746 --> 10:20.271
I can because I'm
here all the time, so.

10:20.315 --> 10:23.318
- No, no, we're good.

10:23.361 --> 10:25.407
I got past that
a long time ago.

10:25.450 --> 10:27.452
It's great to see you, man.

10:27.496 --> 10:31.021
- Thanks, yeah, uh,
sit over here.

10:31.065 --> 10:35.112
Yo, this is Ricky Halstead.

10:35.156 --> 10:38.638
I haven't seen this dude
in forever and a day.

10:38.681 --> 10:43.033
But no finer man to have
next to you in the sandbox.

10:43.077 --> 10:44.948
[tense music]

10:44.992 --> 10:46.776
- Ricky?

10:46.820 --> 10:49.344
Knox just called him
Ricky Halstead, right?

10:49.387 --> 10:51.825
- Yeah, he did.
- What's that about?

10:51.868 --> 10:53.435
- I have no idea.

10:53.478 --> 10:56.003
- Couple old buddies
find each other in here.

10:56.046 --> 10:57.482
You want to share?

10:59.006 --> 11:01.486
- Well, Ricky and I
did two spins together.

11:01.530 --> 11:04.489
- Kunar, Warsaj Kalay,

11:04.533 --> 11:06.100
up and down
the Korangal Valley.

11:06.143 --> 11:08.624
- And that--that's
the valley of death.

11:08.668 --> 11:11.627
And that's, you know, you know.

11:13.324 --> 11:17.285
I got back from that so messed
up I couldn't eat spaghetti.

11:17.328 --> 11:19.243
'Cause the noodles
and the red sauce

11:19.287 --> 11:21.942
looked like guts, you know,
and I wasn't alone.

11:21.985 --> 11:24.727
Most of our guys got--
got pretty messed up.

11:24.771 --> 11:28.383
Everybody except Ricky.

11:28.426 --> 11:30.515
And I mean,
we were getting these

11:30.559 --> 11:32.866
firefights, like--like, two,

11:32.909 --> 11:36.913
three a day, RPGs flying in,
and Halstead is just...

11:36.957 --> 11:38.785
[whistles]

11:38.828 --> 11:43.398
I used to think it's why
this guy became a sniper.

11:43.441 --> 11:46.357
Man, he doesn't have
the same heart rate

11:46.401 --> 11:48.229
as us mere mortals, you know?

11:48.272 --> 11:50.753
Same body temp. Dude's--

11:50.797 --> 11:53.887
guy's like a reptile.

11:53.930 --> 11:55.453
[laughter]

11:55.497 --> 11:56.628
I mean it.

12:02.591 --> 12:03.810
- Later, men!

12:03.853 --> 12:05.899
- Hey, thanks, Alex,
take it easy.

12:07.509 --> 12:08.771
- All right, man.

12:08.815 --> 12:12.035
- Yeah, Ricky, hold up.

12:12.079 --> 12:14.211
Are you doing okay, bro?

12:14.255 --> 12:16.300
There's got to be some
reason you came into the gym

12:16.344 --> 12:18.172
today after all these years.

12:20.261 --> 12:23.568
- Yeah, I don't know.
It's been a hard time.

12:23.612 --> 12:25.179
You know, I'm going through
the process

12:25.222 --> 12:27.572
of moving right now,
and I found some old photos

12:27.616 --> 12:29.574
from when we were in country.

12:29.618 --> 12:31.925
I guess it brought
some stuff up.

12:31.968 --> 12:33.927
- Yeah.

12:33.970 --> 12:36.930
- Look, man, do you--
you want to hang out later?

12:36.973 --> 12:39.497
I can bring the photos over,
you'd get a kick out of them.

12:39.541 --> 12:42.065
We could,
I don't know, whatever,

12:42.109 --> 12:44.981
drink too much, talk about
our screwed up lives.

12:45.025 --> 12:46.896
- [laughs]

12:46.940 --> 12:49.943
- Yeah, I think
I remember how to do that.

12:49.986 --> 12:51.248
- All right, man.

12:51.292 --> 12:52.728
- All right, brother, see you.

12:54.817 --> 12:57.428
- All right, I'm on with Knox
at 18:30

12:57.472 --> 12:58.952
at his house up near Loyola.

12:58.995 --> 13:01.476
So two hours ago, an undercover
from Bomb and Arson

13:01.519 --> 13:02.825
went for a little dog walk.

13:02.869 --> 13:05.045
They had a canine
sniff around Knox's property

13:05.088 --> 13:07.961
for any indications
of bomb making material.

13:08.004 --> 13:09.614
The dog gave a positive
at a vent

13:09.658 --> 13:11.225
coming from the basement,
but passive.

13:11.268 --> 13:13.227
- Okay, not enough
for a search warrant.

13:13.270 --> 13:15.272
- Right, so the plan is,
I'm going to gain access

13:15.316 --> 13:16.491
to Knox's home.

13:16.534 --> 13:18.014
You guys
will be outside in support.

13:18.058 --> 13:20.190
Hopefully, I find
some evidence and then...

13:20.234 --> 13:21.844
- Crash the party.
What's the go word?

13:21.888 --> 13:23.454
- Juniper.
- Good.

13:23.498 --> 13:27.197
So we grab Knox, flip him,
and break this thing open.

13:27.241 --> 13:28.242
Let's do it.

13:30.897 --> 13:32.507
- Jay.

13:32.550 --> 13:34.161
What's the deal
with this Knox guy?

13:35.640 --> 13:37.599
- He's something else.

13:37.642 --> 13:40.689
- You know I can tell
you hate him, right?

13:40.732 --> 13:42.996
- No, I don't
think about him at all.

13:44.519 --> 13:46.738
- It was kind of nice listening
to you talk about the army.

13:46.782 --> 13:49.219
You never do, right, Ricky?

13:49.263 --> 13:51.656
- Don't call me that.

13:51.700 --> 13:55.095
- Okay, I'm sorry.

13:55.138 --> 13:58.576
No, don't apologize either,
just--

13:58.620 --> 14:00.187
just don't call me that.

14:08.369 --> 14:10.893
- Oh, wow.

14:10.937 --> 14:12.286
I forgot about
that pipe hitter.

14:12.329 --> 14:14.462
What's his name?
- Muldoon.

14:14.505 --> 14:15.985
[Knox chuckles]

14:16.029 --> 14:17.944
He's the who actually
thought the army handed out

14:17.987 --> 14:19.946
Camaros when you finish
boot camp.

14:19.989 --> 14:22.862
- He looks like it too.
Look at his face.

14:22.905 --> 14:24.602
- I gotta take a leak.
You want a fresh one?

14:24.646 --> 14:25.995
- Yeah, yeah.

14:26.039 --> 14:27.867
Bathroom's by the front door.

14:29.999 --> 14:31.131
Oh, man.

14:35.700 --> 14:38.616
[suspenseful music]

14:38.660 --> 14:45.754
♪

15:43.203 --> 15:44.639
[door clicks open]

15:48.338 --> 15:50.514
The hell are you doing
down here, Ricky?

15:50.558 --> 15:52.081
- Damn it.

15:52.125 --> 15:54.562
- Get frosty, looks like
he got made.

15:54.605 --> 15:56.346
- Copy you.

15:56.390 --> 15:58.653
- Chaspaki mine, sticky bombs.

16:00.481 --> 16:03.005
You still using juniper trees?

16:03.049 --> 16:04.615
- That's the go word,
let's go.

16:04.659 --> 16:07.618
[intense music]

16:07.662 --> 16:10.404
♪

16:10.447 --> 16:12.972
- It's no business of yours.

16:13.015 --> 16:14.843
- What is all this?

16:14.886 --> 16:16.018
- I think it's time
for you to go, man.

16:16.062 --> 16:17.237
- Dude, are you
in some kind of trouble?

16:17.280 --> 16:19.413
- Right now, Rick.
- Whoa, whoa, okay.

16:19.456 --> 16:20.892
- Come on.
- Okay, man.

16:20.936 --> 16:23.243
- Just move to the door.
- Okay, I'm going.

16:23.286 --> 16:24.635
- Chicago PD!

16:24.679 --> 16:25.593
Where are you?
- Back off!

16:25.636 --> 16:27.682
Basement--basement!

16:28.944 --> 16:30.990
Back up, get against the wall.

16:32.817 --> 16:35.690
I'm a cop, you're under arrest.
Turn around.

16:35.733 --> 16:38.345
Turn around,
put your hands out.

16:38.388 --> 16:40.303
- Jay, you good?

16:40.347 --> 16:41.870
- We're down here!

16:43.350 --> 16:44.742
Do not move.

16:47.571 --> 16:49.399
- This is what do you do
now, huh?

16:49.443 --> 16:52.315
You come into that gym,
you use everybody in there.

16:52.359 --> 16:55.492
Then you come into my home
and you spit in my face.

16:55.536 --> 16:57.016
It's a good fit for you, Ricky.

16:57.059 --> 16:58.321
Lets you chase the past.

16:58.365 --> 16:59.931
- Got nothing to do
with the past.

16:59.975 --> 17:01.150
It's got nothing to do
with me at all.

17:01.194 --> 17:02.412
- Yeah, God forbid
somebody can't live up

17:02.456 --> 17:04.545
to your standards, right?

17:04.588 --> 17:05.894
[phone chimes]
- Let's move.

17:09.332 --> 17:10.812
You might want
to rethink your approach

17:10.855 --> 17:12.379
before we get upstairs.
- Screw you, man.

17:12.422 --> 17:13.684
- There was a little girl
at the bank

17:13.728 --> 17:15.034
when the bomb went off.

17:15.077 --> 17:17.384
- She get hurt?
- She just died.

17:21.779 --> 17:21.997
.

17:22.041 --> 17:23.564
- How old was she?

17:27.568 --> 17:30.179
- Nine.

17:30.223 --> 17:31.920
Name was Sydney Rose.

17:34.096 --> 17:36.098
- How'd she die?

17:36.142 --> 17:37.621
- Shrapnel.

17:39.145 --> 17:40.711
The device you built
killed this kid.

17:40.755 --> 17:42.931
So you know
what happens now, right?

17:42.974 --> 17:44.498
- Yeah, I think I can put
two and two together.

17:44.541 --> 17:46.587
- Okay, good.

17:46.630 --> 17:49.024
- Look, nobody
was supposed to get hurt.

17:49.068 --> 17:50.417
I swear to God that was all--

17:50.460 --> 17:52.332
- Listen, Knox.

17:52.375 --> 17:56.031
The only reason
you're sitting here right now?

17:56.075 --> 17:57.641
'Cause I want to hear
your story.

17:57.685 --> 17:59.252
I mean,
I really want to hear it.

18:01.080 --> 18:02.690
But let me tell you something.

18:04.735 --> 18:09.175
One lie, one omission,

18:09.218 --> 18:11.133
it's game over,

18:11.177 --> 18:13.266
you understand me?
- Yeah.

18:16.704 --> 18:18.009
- Is that you?

18:18.053 --> 18:21.709
[suspenseful music]

18:21.752 --> 18:24.755
- No.
- No.

18:24.799 --> 18:26.235
Is that you?

18:26.279 --> 18:29.543
- No, I swear on my mother's
grave this is not me.

18:29.586 --> 18:33.155
Listen, I make the explosive
devices and then I sell them.

18:33.199 --> 18:34.417
They do the rest.

18:34.461 --> 18:37.420
- Yeah, okay, they.

18:37.464 --> 18:38.726
So who's they?

18:38.769 --> 18:40.119
- I don't know.

18:41.816 --> 18:42.991
I don't know who they are.

18:43.034 --> 18:45.036
Listen to me, I'll help you.

18:45.080 --> 18:46.777
I'll tell you
everything I know.

18:46.821 --> 18:48.170
I meet one guy,
and I sell to him--

18:48.214 --> 18:49.737
- Okay, what's his name?

18:52.566 --> 18:55.482
- Matthew Davis,
29 years old, no priors.

18:55.525 --> 18:58.006
According to Knox,
Davis is his only contact.

18:58.049 --> 18:59.094
- Mm-hm.

18:59.138 --> 19:00.443
And all of Knox's alibis
check out.

19:00.487 --> 19:01.966
He wasn't at one damn robbery.

19:02.010 --> 19:04.186
- So Knox meets with Davis,
but he's not gonna be able

19:04.230 --> 19:06.580
to testify that Davis
is one of the robbers.

19:06.623 --> 19:08.016
- Right, Davis buys the bombs.

19:08.059 --> 19:09.539
Maybe he sells them
to the crew.

19:09.583 --> 19:11.976
- We got a ping order in,
connect Davis to the robberies

19:12.020 --> 19:15.632
that way, but other than that,
we got no proof.

19:15.676 --> 19:17.199
- All right, so bottom line.

19:17.243 --> 19:20.420
We got zero evidence tying
any offender to any of this.

19:20.463 --> 19:22.248
- Sorry for the interruption.

19:22.291 --> 19:24.554
The feds have now
left three messages.

19:24.598 --> 19:25.903
They're looking for you.

19:25.947 --> 19:27.775
They want to confirm
all Roy Walton's vehicles,

19:27.818 --> 19:30.473
make and model.

19:30.517 --> 19:32.301
- Send them the case files.
- That's what I said.

19:32.345 --> 19:34.869
And I'm pretty sure the new
round of fed boys can't read,

19:34.912 --> 19:37.698
nor can they read my tone,
so please call them back.

19:42.050 --> 19:43.356
- Everything good, boss?

19:45.184 --> 19:48.491
- Yeah, they're just confirming
for their bulletins.

19:48.535 --> 19:50.841
Okay, so we use Davis.

19:50.885 --> 19:53.192
I mean, Knox is already
fully cooperating.

19:53.235 --> 19:55.498
We have him reach out to Davis,
sell him some explosives.

19:55.542 --> 19:57.326
We keep flipping on up.

19:57.370 --> 19:58.893
All right, Jay,
advise State's Attorney

19:58.936 --> 20:00.851
we got a cooperating defendant.
- Yeah.

20:00.895 --> 20:03.202
- Hailey, brief Knox,
wire him up.

20:06.770 --> 20:07.902
- Before you meet up
with Davis,

20:07.945 --> 20:09.860
hold this button down,

20:09.904 --> 20:12.298
and then this
indicator light will come up.

20:12.341 --> 20:13.603
That's it.

20:13.647 --> 20:15.126
Can you say something?

20:17.912 --> 20:20.654
- So you're Halstead's partner,
huh?

20:20.697 --> 20:22.351
- Yep.

20:22.395 --> 20:24.788
- Guess you must
know him pretty good.

20:24.832 --> 20:27.487
- Pretty good.

20:27.530 --> 20:29.228
- I love that guy,
you know.

20:30.664 --> 20:32.100
Even now.

20:33.710 --> 20:36.060
We had a good thing,
back in the day.

20:36.104 --> 20:38.715
[sentimental music]

20:38.759 --> 20:41.109
- What happened?

20:42.893 --> 20:45.244
- War happened.

20:47.768 --> 20:53.991
I made a mistake,
and it was bad.

20:54.035 --> 20:56.516
One look at Ricky's face,
I knew it was bad.

20:59.606 --> 21:01.477
It's the job, you know?

21:01.521 --> 21:04.001
Puts you in these places
where the right thing

21:04.045 --> 21:07.831
is wrong and the wrong
thing is--is right.

21:11.618 --> 21:14.273
[phone buzzes]

21:15.752 --> 21:16.927
Matthew Davis.

21:16.971 --> 21:19.930
[suspenseful music]

21:19.974 --> 21:27.111
♪

21:40.821 --> 21:42.866
- So what happens now?

21:42.910 --> 21:45.347
- You go home, you wait.

21:45.391 --> 21:46.566
You hope the crew
gets back in touch with you

21:46.609 --> 21:48.089
or we find another way.

21:48.132 --> 21:49.830
But above all else you
hope like hell I don't find out

21:49.873 --> 21:52.180
that you tipped them off.

21:52.223 --> 21:54.617
- That's what you think
happened here?

21:54.661 --> 21:57.794
- If you didn't, explain to me
why they pulled the plug.

21:57.838 --> 22:00.971
- Because I'm expendable,
Ricky.

22:01.015 --> 22:03.974
To the army,
to these guys, to you.

22:04.018 --> 22:05.628
You watch,
soon as my use expires

22:05.672 --> 22:06.760
you'll kick me to the curb.

22:06.803 --> 22:08.065
- I'm bringing you home,
aren't I?

22:08.109 --> 22:09.328
You're free man, right?
- Come on, man.

22:09.371 --> 22:11.025
We know the terms of my deal.

22:11.068 --> 22:13.332
I get to stay a free man
if you find the robbery crew,

22:13.375 --> 22:15.638
and right now, as nearly
as I can tell, you got nothing.

22:15.682 --> 22:17.814
- Shut up.

22:17.858 --> 22:20.426
Get out of the car, go inside,
and you wait by the phone.

22:20.469 --> 22:22.166
You answer it on the
first ring, you understand me?

22:22.210 --> 22:23.820
You do anything stupid,
I'm gonna slap the cuffs

22:23.864 --> 22:25.822
back on you myself.

22:25.866 --> 22:27.346
Get out of my car.

22:29.565 --> 22:31.001
- Yes, sir.

22:35.571 --> 22:37.051
- Little harsh.

22:38.792 --> 22:40.576
- You don't know him like I do.

22:40.620 --> 22:43.492
- No, but he was making
some sense to me.

22:43.536 --> 22:44.711
- Units on the citywide,

22:44.754 --> 22:46.234
we have
an armed robbery in progress.

22:46.277 --> 22:48.279
Armored vehicle,
North Park Bank,

22:48.323 --> 22:49.846
Catalpa and Winchester.

22:49.890 --> 22:50.847
- You gotta be kidding me.

22:50.891 --> 22:52.849
- Go, go, go.

22:52.893 --> 22:56.418
[intense music]

22:56.462 --> 22:59.421
[gunfire]

23:01.423 --> 23:02.685
- Get down!

23:02.729 --> 23:03.860
Get down!

23:03.904 --> 23:05.558
[person screams]

23:08.822 --> 23:10.389
- 50-21 Henry, 10-1, 10-1!

23:10.432 --> 23:12.173
Shots fired at the police.
We got one down.

23:12.216 --> 23:14.001
- Police coming up behind you!
Stay back, stay back!

23:14.044 --> 23:15.655
We need ambo and cars now!

23:17.221 --> 23:18.092
- Where's the other two?
- Gone!

23:18.135 --> 23:19.528
They left his ass behind.

23:25.752 --> 23:27.275
[tires squeal]

23:33.412 --> 23:35.457
- You two behind me!
Get behind the car!

23:35.501 --> 23:37.633
- Hailey, I'm moving!
- Go! I got you!

23:39.330 --> 23:41.463
- Stay down! Stay down.

23:41.507 --> 23:48.209
♪

24:07.097 --> 24:08.359
- Stop the car!

24:08.403 --> 24:10.623
Get out of the car now!

24:10.666 --> 24:11.841
Get out of the car.

24:11.885 --> 24:14.061
[driver screams]

24:28.815 --> 24:29.250
.

24:29.293 --> 24:33.167
[indistinct chatter]

24:33.210 --> 24:35.691
- What do we got?
- MO's completely changed.

24:35.735 --> 24:36.997
They didn't even try
to blow the doors

24:37.040 --> 24:38.389
off the truck this time.

24:38.433 --> 24:40.043
Instead, they executed
a guard who was pushing

24:40.087 --> 24:41.654
a cart of cash into the bank.

24:41.697 --> 24:43.612
- That's why it went south.
- Yeah, it became a shootout.

24:43.656 --> 24:45.396
Two offenders
managed to take off.

24:45.440 --> 24:47.790
Third guy couldn't get to them,
so they left him.

24:47.834 --> 24:49.488
- Okay, so why the new MO?

24:49.531 --> 24:51.533
- Apparently, the companies
got together and decided

24:51.577 --> 24:53.709
to add a third guard
to the back of the trucks.

24:53.753 --> 24:55.798
It's a new policy that
they decided to announce

24:55.842 --> 24:57.408
publicly as a deterrent.

24:57.452 --> 24:59.454
- That way if a crew blew
the truck from the outside,

24:59.498 --> 25:00.934
then the third guard
can engage from inside

25:00.977 --> 25:02.326
before they could get in.

25:02.370 --> 25:04.459
- Yeah, it's the only card
they had left to play.

25:04.503 --> 25:05.721
- Yeah, it makes sense.

25:05.765 --> 25:08.637
It's more violent,
messier, but in theory,

25:08.681 --> 25:10.247
it gets them
in and out quickly.

25:10.291 --> 25:12.206
- All right, talk to me.

25:12.249 --> 25:13.860
- Our dead offender
is Paul McBride.

25:13.903 --> 25:15.818
23, relatively short sheet.

25:15.862 --> 25:18.212
But his cousin Cooper McBride,
he's a heavy hitter.

25:18.255 --> 25:20.910
- Cooper did six years for
pulling cartridges out of ATMs.

25:20.954 --> 25:22.912
Now, he hasn't been heard
from since he got out,

25:22.956 --> 25:24.740
but Cooper is six feet tall.

25:24.784 --> 25:27.003
- Which matches the body type
of one of our offenders.

25:27.047 --> 25:28.178
I mean, it's got to be him.

25:28.222 --> 25:29.963
It's got to be
Cooper McBride's crew.

25:30.006 --> 25:33.357
- Yeah, except we still
got zero hard evidence.

25:33.401 --> 25:35.621
All right, let's scrub
the bodies for DNA.

25:37.492 --> 25:39.059
- Hey, Sarge, Knox
was a fail.

25:39.102 --> 25:41.452
I say we sent him downstate,
we just start fresh.

25:41.496 --> 25:43.542
- Hold on,
Knox was not a fail.

25:43.585 --> 25:45.631
He didn't get made,
he didn't make a mistake.

25:45.674 --> 25:47.589
The only reason
the robbery crew ghosted him

25:47.633 --> 25:49.548
is because they stopped
using bombs.

25:49.591 --> 25:50.766
I think we should
double down on him.

25:50.810 --> 25:51.898
- No way.

25:51.941 --> 25:53.595
- Look, you guys
have your own history,

25:53.639 --> 25:55.597
and that's what
you're judging him on.

25:55.641 --> 25:57.643
But these guys,
this robbery crew?

25:57.686 --> 26:01.211
They can't keep doing this,
they have to find a better way.

26:01.255 --> 26:03.039
What they need
is somebody to help them

26:03.083 --> 26:04.301
with the third guard.

26:04.345 --> 26:06.652
So what they
really need is a sniper.

26:08.654 --> 26:10.481
- Look, Jay,
I get you got a problem

26:10.525 --> 26:12.614
with this guy,
but unless you got another way,

26:12.658 --> 26:13.920
Knox is it.

26:13.963 --> 26:16.531
So what's it gonna be?

26:24.670 --> 26:26.541
- What the hell
am I doing back here?

26:26.585 --> 26:28.804
You arrest these guys or what?

26:28.848 --> 26:30.414
- New plan.

26:30.458 --> 26:32.721
You're gonna introduce me
to Davis as a sniper for hire.

26:34.375 --> 26:36.856
You know how to find Davis?

26:36.899 --> 26:39.075
- Yeah, I mean,
his family's owned the bar

26:39.119 --> 26:40.163
for, like, a million years.

26:40.207 --> 26:41.556
He's always
hanging around there.

26:43.123 --> 26:45.516
- Can you get this done?

26:45.560 --> 26:47.170
- Well, the alternative
is life in prison?

26:47.214 --> 26:49.216
Yeah, I can do this.

26:52.393 --> 26:54.351
- Look at us, huh?

26:54.395 --> 26:56.223
Brothers in arms again.

26:58.355 --> 27:00.967
- Let's clear
something up right now.

27:01.010 --> 27:03.273
You made the wrong call
in Afghanistan.

27:03.317 --> 27:04.840
So did I.

27:04.884 --> 27:08.670
And I haven't forgotten
any of it.

27:08.714 --> 27:10.280
And I just hope to hell
that we're not making

27:10.324 --> 27:11.630
the wrong call right now.

27:11.673 --> 27:13.501
- Everything's so black
and white with you.

27:13.544 --> 27:15.590
Some of us aren't so lucky.

27:17.374 --> 27:20.160
- Just do this one right,
you hear me?

27:20.203 --> 27:22.553
It's all I'm asking of you.
- I will.

27:22.597 --> 27:26.340
I got your back, Ricky, I do.

27:26.383 --> 27:29.299
[apprehensive music]

27:29.343 --> 27:36.480
♪

27:39.745 --> 27:43.400
- Matthew, how you doing, man?

27:43.444 --> 27:45.272
- What are you doing here,
Knox?

27:45.315 --> 27:46.795
I told you we ain't buying.

27:46.839 --> 27:49.015
- I'm not here for that.
And I'm not alone.

27:50.930 --> 27:52.366
- You kidding?

27:52.409 --> 27:53.715
You don't bring people here.

27:53.759 --> 27:55.674
- Calm down, I saw what
happened on the TV.

27:55.717 --> 27:57.414
- I don't know what
you're talking about.

27:57.458 --> 27:59.416
- I'm trying to make a connect.
- You better shut up right now.

27:59.460 --> 28:00.766
- Me and him
were in the army together.

28:00.809 --> 28:03.029
The guy's a sniper,
best I ever saw.

28:03.072 --> 28:04.291
- I don't care who he is.

28:04.334 --> 28:05.901
- All right, okay, I get it.

28:05.945 --> 28:08.382
But I don't think yelling and
grabbing your piece in a bar

28:08.425 --> 28:10.166
is gonna get you exactly--
- We own this bar!

28:10.210 --> 28:13.604
- How about
he talks and you listen?

28:13.648 --> 28:16.520
- You can't risk blowing
the trucks anymore, right?

28:16.564 --> 28:18.174
And this whole plan
you came up with of taking

28:18.218 --> 28:19.610
the guard out point blank?

28:19.654 --> 28:23.092
It's stupid, it's a mess,
so you're out of the game.

28:23.136 --> 28:27.488
If you hire me, I can take him
out from 300, 400 yards away.

28:27.531 --> 28:29.795
You grab the goods,
it's over before they know

28:29.838 --> 28:31.884
it started, and you
get to keep making money.

28:33.886 --> 28:37.019
- What, you do this
for a living?

28:37.063 --> 28:38.760
You're a professional sniper?

28:38.804 --> 28:40.544
- No, man,
I ain't a professional nothing.

28:40.588 --> 28:42.416
I got back
from the war with ability

28:42.459 --> 28:45.114
and skills that don't
translate to much.

28:45.158 --> 28:49.510
Cut me and Knox in for a piece,
everybody wins.

28:51.860 --> 28:54.820
[tense music]

28:54.863 --> 29:01.740
♪

29:24.545 --> 29:25.894
- Come on.

29:39.386 --> 29:41.562
- Prove it.

29:41.605 --> 29:43.520
- Prove what?

29:43.564 --> 29:45.392
- Prove you can take the shot.

29:49.135 --> 29:51.485
See the truck?

29:51.528 --> 29:52.834
Find the smiley face.

29:54.705 --> 29:56.533
- What, from here?

29:56.577 --> 29:58.318
- It's a quarter mile,
is that a problem?

29:58.361 --> 30:05.499
♪

30:21.080 --> 30:22.559
- Where do you want it?

30:22.603 --> 30:25.606
- How about the left eye?

30:25.649 --> 30:27.782
- His left?

30:27.826 --> 30:29.088
- Sure.

30:45.713 --> 30:47.149
- He's not going to make it.

30:47.193 --> 30:49.195
- [laughs]

30:49.238 --> 30:51.719
- You know what we do?

30:51.762 --> 30:53.503
I've had my eye on a job.

30:53.547 --> 30:54.896
It's a truck that
services poker rooms.

30:54.940 --> 30:57.203
Lands at a bank,
that's a hell of a lot of cash.

30:57.246 --> 31:01.207
I didn't think we'd be able
to do the job, but with you...

31:01.250 --> 31:02.469
- You'll all be fine.

31:02.512 --> 31:05.298
- Great.

31:05.341 --> 31:07.691
- But if you miss the shot,
or if anything goes wrong

31:07.735 --> 31:09.606
at all, we kill him,
you understand?

31:09.650 --> 31:13.262
I put him down like a dog.

31:13.306 --> 31:15.569
- I won't miss. Come on.

31:15.612 --> 31:22.750
♪

31:58.568 --> 32:00.744
- You talk to the Feds yet?

32:00.788 --> 32:02.355
- Yeah, like I said,
it was nothing.

32:02.398 --> 32:04.444
Just for the bulletins.

32:04.487 --> 32:06.968
- Where is he?

32:07.012 --> 32:09.318
Roy's body.

32:09.362 --> 32:11.712
Two bullets from my
service weapon are in him.

32:11.755 --> 32:13.975
- No, they're not.

32:14.019 --> 32:17.152
I policed your slugs,
handled the rest.

32:17.196 --> 32:18.719
It's done.

32:20.373 --> 32:22.984
- I have a right to know.

32:23.028 --> 32:25.595
- You don't need
another secret to hold onto.

32:26.945 --> 32:28.337
- Sarge, we have problems.

32:28.381 --> 32:29.860
- Go ahead.

32:29.904 --> 32:31.688
- TACT team says the
armored vehicle is on track,

32:31.732 --> 32:32.907
they should be here any minute,

32:32.951 --> 32:34.474
but there's no sign
of the robbery crew.

32:34.517 --> 32:35.736
They're late.

32:35.779 --> 32:36.911
- Just let it play.

32:36.955 --> 32:38.782
Vehicle's not here yet.

32:38.826 --> 32:40.697
- That's not all.

32:40.741 --> 32:42.482
Knox is at the crew's place.

32:42.525 --> 32:44.136
- Well, how the hell
do you know that?

32:44.179 --> 32:46.834
- Because I
put a tracker on his car.

32:46.877 --> 32:48.575
I texted him to say
I'm in position at the bank,

32:48.618 --> 32:50.098
I called, still nothing.

32:50.142 --> 32:53.058
So either he's playing us,
or he got made.

32:54.885 --> 32:56.757
- All right, Adam, Kim,
you hold anchor here.

32:56.800 --> 32:58.802
Jay, Kev,
you're with us, let's go.

32:58.846 --> 33:01.762
[intense music]

33:01.805 --> 33:08.203
♪

33:08.247 --> 33:10.292
- Knox's car is out front.
- Copy.

33:18.431 --> 33:20.955
- Jay, Kev, you hit the front.

33:20.999 --> 33:23.479
Hailey, you got the left,
I got the right, let's go.

33:23.523 --> 33:24.654
- Copy that.

33:31.139 --> 33:34.055
- I got a body.

33:34.099 --> 33:35.578
- Hailey.

33:35.622 --> 33:36.971
- Yeah, hey.

33:38.929 --> 33:41.584
It's Cooper McBride.

33:41.628 --> 33:43.847
He was executed, close range.

33:48.156 --> 33:51.116
- They pulled
out his fingernails.

33:51.159 --> 33:53.074
- Not they.

33:53.118 --> 33:54.293
Knox.

33:54.336 --> 33:56.034
- What?
[gunshots]

33:56.077 --> 33:58.297
- Sarge?!

33:58.340 --> 34:00.081
Sarge, are you hit?
Are you good?

34:00.125 --> 34:01.648
- I'm good!

34:01.691 --> 34:04.259
Got a live one here.

34:04.303 --> 34:06.783
Lobbed a few at me.

34:06.827 --> 34:09.047
Show me your hands, real slow!

34:11.049 --> 34:13.051
Come on out, drop it!

34:18.752 --> 34:20.884
- It's Davis.

34:20.928 --> 34:23.887
- Thank God, I thought
you were Knox.

34:25.628 --> 34:28.022
Please, help me.

34:37.945 --> 34:38.293
.

34:38.337 --> 34:39.860
[Davis groaning]

34:39.903 --> 34:42.123
- Clear, nobody else in there.
- Here.

34:42.167 --> 34:43.951
- Just hang tight,
ambulance is on the way.

34:43.994 --> 34:46.040
Just tell us what happened.

34:46.084 --> 34:48.434
- We were packing for the job.

34:48.477 --> 34:52.133
Knox, he showed up over here.

34:52.177 --> 34:54.527
Walked up and shot me,
left me to die.

34:54.570 --> 34:56.137
Made McBride tell him
where the money is

34:56.181 --> 34:57.791
from the other job.

34:57.834 --> 34:59.314
I don't know what
the hell he did to him.

34:59.358 --> 35:00.359
McBride was screaming.

35:00.402 --> 35:01.534
- Where is he,
where is Knox?

35:01.577 --> 35:03.188
- He took off
in one of our cars.

35:03.231 --> 35:04.711
- What car?
- It's some junker van.

35:04.754 --> 35:06.060
I don't know!

35:06.104 --> 35:07.409
There's cars in and out
of here all the time.

35:07.453 --> 35:09.368
- Where's he headed?
Where do you keep the money?

35:09.411 --> 35:13.459
[suspenseful music]

35:13.502 --> 35:15.417
- Jay, Hailey,
closing on your position.

35:15.461 --> 35:16.853
Five minutes out.

35:16.897 --> 35:18.812
- I'm two minutes behind.

35:18.855 --> 35:20.379
- Crew's unit's down there.

35:22.120 --> 35:23.425
- It's open at both ends.

35:25.210 --> 35:26.515
- Why don't you drop me off
around here

35:26.559 --> 35:28.256
then go around the side,
and meet in the middle.

35:28.300 --> 35:35.437
♪

36:09.819 --> 36:11.908
- Get your hands in the air,
get on your knees now!

36:13.562 --> 36:15.347
Hands in the air, Knox.

36:18.001 --> 36:19.525
Hands in the air, now!

36:25.574 --> 36:28.621
Drop your weapon now
and get on your knees!

36:28.664 --> 36:31.580
Drop your weapon
and get on your knees!

36:31.624 --> 36:33.713
- I've been
on my knees a long time.

36:33.756 --> 36:35.454
- Put the gun down.

36:35.497 --> 36:37.195
- I had my chance,
I had to take it.

36:37.238 --> 36:39.153
- You killed a guy.

36:39.197 --> 36:40.850
- World's a better place
because of it.

36:40.894 --> 36:42.156
- Doesn't work like that.

36:42.200 --> 36:43.984
- Right, you know how it works.

36:44.027 --> 36:46.595
That's not for someone
like me to understand, huh,

36:46.639 --> 36:48.945
'cause, let's just face it,
I'm just meat.

36:48.989 --> 36:50.512
- Put the gun down.

36:50.556 --> 36:52.079
- Here, have this skill,
but don't use it like that.

36:52.122 --> 36:54.168
And take this rifle and kill
him, but don't kill him!

36:54.212 --> 36:55.735
- Put your weapon down!

36:55.778 --> 36:57.258
- And come along
on the robbery job, Knox,

36:57.302 --> 36:58.390
and we'll just decide later
if we want

36:58.433 --> 37:01.480
to kill you
like a dog afterwards.

37:01.523 --> 37:05.005
But don't you think,
boy, don't you do that.

37:05.048 --> 37:07.486
Don't you decide what's right
and what's wrong

37:07.529 --> 37:09.575
and what's fair
and who deserves what,

37:09.618 --> 37:13.274
'cause that
is for somebody else.

37:13.318 --> 37:14.841
- I'm going to say this
one more time,

37:14.884 --> 37:16.582
put the gun down
and get on your knees,

37:16.625 --> 37:18.497
or I will kill you
if I have to.

37:21.021 --> 37:22.675
- You feel that?

37:22.718 --> 37:25.155
You do exactly as she says
and keep your mouth shut,

37:25.199 --> 37:27.419
or the next thing that comes
out of it's gonna be a bullet.

37:29.247 --> 37:30.857
- Get on your knees, now.

37:36.384 --> 37:38.343
[gun clatters on ground]

37:38.386 --> 37:40.519
- Hands out!
- All right, all right.

37:41.737 --> 37:44.000
Damn it, I wanted to help you,

37:44.044 --> 37:46.916
Ricky, I--I really did.

37:48.788 --> 37:51.399
This just felt right.
- Get up.

37:53.575 --> 37:55.751
- 50-21 Henry,
offender's in custody.

38:02.802 --> 38:04.586
- I'm sorry
for holding things back.

38:06.719 --> 38:10.897
I know I don't talk about
my time in the army that much.

38:10.940 --> 38:13.421
It's not that I want to keep
anything from you, it's just...

38:15.641 --> 38:18.339
- You don't
have to tell me anything.

38:18.383 --> 38:21.255
You can,
and I'll love you all the same.

38:21.299 --> 38:24.432
[pensive music]

38:24.476 --> 38:26.608
- "Ricky" is short
for "Ricochet."

38:28.697 --> 38:31.700
One day, outside the wire...

38:34.442 --> 38:36.575
I shot a guy 400 yards away

38:36.618 --> 38:41.231
by bouncing a round off
of an armored Humvee.

38:41.275 --> 38:43.930
My guys didn't think
I could make it.

38:43.973 --> 38:45.410
The name stuck.

38:46.889 --> 38:47.977
And I liked it.

38:53.331 --> 38:55.768
- What about Knox?

38:55.811 --> 38:59.424
He said he did something,
he made a mistake?

39:03.950 --> 39:08.824
- There was a guy in our
unit that everybody loved.

39:08.868 --> 39:12.741
His name was Lopez,
and he couldn't resist

39:12.785 --> 39:16.441
handing out candy to all
the local kids on base.

39:17.964 --> 39:20.358
So the Taliban used
a kid to kill him.

39:22.751 --> 39:25.624
And Knox decided to take
matters into his own hands,

39:25.667 --> 39:30.324
so he went out one night,
off the books,

39:30.368 --> 39:33.893
and he found
the man responsible.

39:33.936 --> 39:37.418
And he killed everyone
in the house.

39:42.336 --> 39:43.990
Everyone.

39:47.428 --> 39:48.560
- Knox wasn't charged, though.

39:48.603 --> 39:50.605
He served out his tour.

39:52.477 --> 39:55.175
- Yeah, he covered it up.

39:55.218 --> 39:57.438
He lied.

39:59.658 --> 40:05.315
The truth is,
I could have done something.

40:05.359 --> 40:06.882
I should have.

40:08.928 --> 40:10.886
And I didn't.

40:17.066 --> 40:20.418
I like that he told you it was
a mistake, though, that's good.

40:22.332 --> 40:24.422
He probably believes that too.

40:26.728 --> 40:28.774
It's insane
what we tell ourselves.

40:30.515 --> 40:32.517
And it was straight up murder.

40:35.563 --> 40:37.217
It was murder and lies.

40:37.260 --> 40:44.442
♪

40:47.227 --> 40:51.144
Well, confession can
definitely make you hungry.

40:53.363 --> 40:54.887
You got anything
you want to share?

41:00.458 --> 41:02.372
- I'm an open book,
you know that.

41:02.416 --> 41:09.467
♪

41:16.778 --> 41:19.912
[suspenseful music]

41:19.955 --> 41:26.875
♪

41:46.982 --> 41:49.942
[wolf howls]
